# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
*.egg
build/
dist/
.eggs/
pip-wheel-metadata/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
.venv-*/
venv/
ENV/

# uv
uv.lock.* # backups, never the lockfile itself

# Tooling caches
.ruff_cache/
.pyrefly_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.cache/

# Editor
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
.DS_Store

# iCloud / CloudDocs conflict copies — macOS Finder mints `<name> 2.<ext>`
# files when the iCloud daemon sees a touched-then-resynced file. They are
# stale snapshots, never useful in version control.
* 2.md
* 2.py
* 2.yml
* 2.yaml
* 2.json
* 2.toml

# Nightly runtime — left intentionally untracked here as a sensible default.
# Per .planning/brainstorm.html §04, this is the user's preference, not Nightly's
# requirement. Delete this line if you want session logs in version control.
.nightly/runs/
.nightly/atlas/
.nightly/memory/
.nightly/bugs/

# Claude Code per-developer local state — `settings.local.json` is the
# Stop-hook config (literally "local"), `skills/` is regenerated by
# `nightly init`, and `worktrees/` holds throwaway nested repo checkouts
# (~MB-scale). Nothing here is shareable across contributors. Equivalent
# directories from sibling hosts (Codex / Cursor / Antigravity / Gemini /
# opencode) are excluded by `proposers` — see `proposers/base.py` #13.
.claude/
.codex/
.cursor/
.antigravity/
.gemini/
.opencode/

# Document-orchestrator intermediate drafts. Useful as an audit trail
# locally; not worth versioning. Final artifact is the committed file
# (e.g. README.md), not the iteration snapshots.
.planning/drafts/
